The paper is about Named Entity Recognition (NER), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and falls under the Computer Science category. The use of neural models and pre-trained embeddings suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on improving NER performance with minimal computational cost suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the potential application of these techniques to other tasks and datasets suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) where similar techniques are used for image recognition tasks.
